            },
            "answer_text": "It isn\u2019t determined by page count, because page count can be manipulated easily by shrinking or enlarging text, changing line spacing, or altering margins or page sizes. Word count is used, instead. A standard novella is anything from about 20,000 to 40,000 words. However, this varies somewhat by genre. In some genres, like science fiction or fantasy, where novels routinely tend to longer word-counts, a novella might also be expected to be on the longer side, while in genres where novels are routinely on the shorter side (a romance or cozy mystery novel, for instance), the novellas also tend to the shorter side. How Long Should Your Novel Be? Our Editors Have the Answers ",
